    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Chromosome 22 is the second smallest of the 23 pairs of chromosomes in the nucleus of every human cell, and it comprises only about 1.7 percent of the DNA in the human genome, but in many ways it shows what it means to have the sequence of the entire human genome.</p>
      </block>
